'''Jaroslav Zelený''' (born 20 August 1992) is a Czech professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[left-back]] or [[centre-back]] for [[AC Sparta Prague|Sparta Prague]] and the [[Czech Republic national football team|Czech Republic national team]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ceskenoviny.cz/zpravy/prvni-letni-posilou-slavie-je-schranz-opacnym-smerem-miri-malinsky-a-zeleny/2048486|title=První letní posilou Slavie je Schranz, opačným směrem míří Malínský a Zelený}}</ref>

==Career==
On 3 June 2022, Zelený signed a contract with [[AC Sparta Prague|Sparta Prague]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Sparta má druhou posilu. Zelený podepsal víceletou smlouvu|url=https://isport.blesk.cz/clanek/fotbal-1-liga-rocnik-2022-23/415077/sparta-ma-druhou-posilu-zeleny-podepsal-viceletou-smlouvu.html|website=[[Blesk]]|publisher=[[Czech News Center]]|agency=[[Czech News Agency]]|date=3 June 2022|language=cs}}</ref>

On 6 September 2020, Zelený received his first invitation to the Czech senior team for the [[2020–21 UEFA Nations League]] match against [[Scotland national football team|Scotland]].<ref>{{Cite news|first=Martin|last=Sedlák|title=V české lize je řada kvalitních hráčů, říká Zelený po duelu se Skotskem|url=https://www.idnes.cz/fotbal/reprezentace/cesko-skotsko-jaroslav-zeleny.A200910_570165_fot_reprez_rou|website=[[Mladá fronta Dnes]]|publisher=[[Mafra (company)|Mafra]]|date=10 September 2020|language=cs}}</ref>

